JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 54
IS  - 3
SP  - 473
EP  - 483
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - I use an equilibrium model of job matchings with a Nash wage equation to derive the response of wages and unemployment to productivity shocks. By endogenising labour's threat point, I show that wages absorb fully permanent shock but only partially temporary shocks. Hence, unemployment responds to perceived temporary shocks but not to permanent shocks.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297570
ER  - 



